# RayLua Linux Version

This file is for Dave. It documents how this Linux-oriented `RayLua` variant was built locally and how to reproduce that build on another Linux machine.

## What was verified

The `RayGame` target was compiled successfully as a native Linux build from this repository.

Verified target:

- `RayLua/build/RayGame`

Verified configuration:

- generator: `Ninja`
- C compiler: `gcc`
- C++ compiler: `g++`
- Lua support: disabled for the verified build
- Duke target: disabled for the verified build

## Required dependencies

Install these before configuring the project:

- `gcc`
- `g++`
- `cmake`
- `ninja`
- `pkg-config`
- `raylib` development package
- OpenGL development libraries

Depending on the distro, `raylib` will also pull the usual windowing/runtime dependencies used by raylib on Linux, such as X11/GL-related packages.

If you want Lua enabled later, you will also need:

- `luajit`
- LuaJIT headers/dev package

## Vendored dependencies used by this project

This tree also uses local copies of:

- `RayLua/External/imgui`
- `RayLua/External/rlImGui`

These are part of the project layout used for this Linux build.

## Configure

From the repository root:

```bash
cmake -S RayLua -B RayLua/build -G Ninja \
  -DCMAKE_C_COMPILER=gcc \
  -DCMAKE_CXX_COMPILER=g++ \
  -DDISABLE_LUA=ON \
  -DBUILD_DUKEGAME=OFF
```

## Build

```bash
cmake --build RayLua/build -j4
```

## Why these flags were used

- `-DDISABLE_LUA=ON`
  The verified Linux build did not rely on LuaJIT. The old flow was Windows/MSVC-oriented, so Lua was disabled for the known-good Linux build.

- `-DBUILD_DUKEGAME=OFF`
  The Linux work in this tree was validated against `RayGame`, not `DukeGame`.

## Run

```bash
./RayLua/build/RayGame
```

You can also pass a map path:

```bash
./RayLua/build/RayGame /path/to/your.map
```

## Asset expectations at runtime

For maps to load correctly, the runtime data directory is expected to contain:

- `palette.dat`
- `TILES*.ART`

Optional extra content may also be used depending on the map/setup.

## Linux-specific changes already present in this branch

- Standard `CMakeLists.txt` entry for `RayLua`
- Linux/OpenGL linkage in CMake
- case-sensitive path fixes such as `Core` vs `core`
- Windows-specific include/path cleanup
- several portability fixes for GCC/Clang
- runtime path handling that is more tolerant on Linux filesystems

## Notes

- This README only documents the Linux build flow that was actually verified locally.
- `RayGame` is the known-good Linux target in this version.
- If Dave wants to enable Lua or build other targets, that should be treated as follow-up work rather than assumed to already be verified.
